race.comment: BERRY BERRY GOOD (1) went forward and proved too strong last time out, scoring by 3.5L over 1000m at Leinster. Some query over the longer sprint but in his current form, he's likely to be winning again. SHASFA (6) was in contention all the way in the same contest but was found wanting late. Has to run out the longer trip as well but is going well enough to get into the finish. HOOCHIE GUCCI (5) comes back 200m off narrow defeats. Peaks and is a chance to deliver his second win. CITY MISTRESS (3) has not won for a long while but his form at York and Toodyay prior to the latest reads well. She can't be ruled out. DEAL OBTAINED (4) was better last time and will be around the mark.
